      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANELO (2) drew a wide gate last start and was never a genuine threat, beaten 19 metres into ninth at this track over 2130m. Will enjoy a nice run from this more favourable starting position and has the talent to find the winners' list from the low draw. DUNCAN TWENTYTWO (11) finished sixth last start over 1730m here, beaten 10 metres, after a good third at Bunbury the run prior. Should enjoy a nice smother from this draw and will be looking for a split at some stage. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back straight away. WRITE RITE RIGHT (5) must be considered after he finished runner-up when resuming over 2100m at Bunbury a week-and-a-half ago. Top-three commodity. VYBRANT (1) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish second at Pinjarra over 1177m. A must for the multiples from the coveted pegs draw.",
